      </ul>

      On the other hand, we show that, outside of two-player zero-sum stochastic games/MARL settings, stationary Markov equilibrium computation (and learning) is intractable. Indeed, not only is stationary Markov <i>Nash</i> equilibrium computation
      intractable but <i>even Coarse Correlated equilibrium computation is intractable</i>. This is true even when the game is known to the agents, there are only two agents, and the discount factor is 1/2, i.e. the game is expected to last for two rounds.
